column16: The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions.  The grants are transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell, and that have no bearer mapped to a QCI with VoIP serviceType.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: It is pegged when a unicast UL grant is transmitted to a UE that uses this cell as the primary cell and does not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, excluding the UL grants for message 3 for RRC connection setup. It is not pegged if corresponding UL data transmission is expected.\nThe counter is pegged when licenses for both CarrierAggregation and EnhancedPdcchLa are enabled, and CarrierAggregation feature is activated.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
Total number of non-privileged RRC connection requests rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: When a non-privileged RRC connection request is rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control.

column16: Number of UE Context Fetch procedures successfully completed during SRVCC handover to GERAN execution.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: X2 UE Context Release message is received from target eNodeB after successful UE Context Fetch procedure. UE Context Fetch procedure was triggered during SRVCC handover to GERAN execution.

column16: Monitors the UL interference level for subframe 2.\nUnit: pW\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The aggregated measured UL interference and noise corresponding to subframe 2.

column16: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRAN based on A2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRQ.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: A RRC Connection Release with redirect information to WCDMA or TD-SCDMA when triggered by A2_Search, A2_Outer_Search or A2_Critical measurement report with RSRQ.

column16: The total number of successful initial E-RAB Establishments with Privileged Access. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at sending of Initial Context Setup Response for each successfully setup E-RAB that has the given ARP Priority Level equal to or below AdmissionControl::paArpOverride.

column16: The uplink volume transfer time used for uplink UE throughput. It comprises of time periods up to the fourth MAC SDU data reception of an uplink buffer transfer on Uu until the buffer is emptied, including the TTI emptying the buffer.\nUnit: ms\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Continuous measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level.

column16: The number of RRC Connection Reestablishment attempts.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: A RRC Connection Reestablishment Request message is received.

column16: Total of successfully received data volume on MAC-level in the UL for SCell traffic, that is, the UE has another cell as its PCell CC. This counter includes possible padding bits.\nUnit: kilobit (1 000 bits)\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented when a UL transmission is acknowledged on HARQ-level, that is, only stepped for SCell CC traffic.

column16: The total number of abnormal UE context releases initiated by the RBS due to pre-emption and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped for each UE that is released due to pre-emption when data was in either the UL or DL buffer.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nCompressed: True\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

For inter-eNodeB (IeNb) carrier aggregation interactions, records the mean number of UEs that have data scheduled on a DL external SCell (ESCell), counted by the number of component carriers hosted on external eNodeBs and simultaneously scheduled.
UE is considered scheduled for carrier aggregation if the eNodeB has sent a PDCCH assignment indicating a PDSCH assignment. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.

PDF ranges:
[0]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have zero scheduled EScell. Includes scheduling only on PCell or SCells.
[1]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have one simultaneously scheduled EScell.
[2]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have two simultaneously scheduled EScells.
[3]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have three simultaneously scheduled EScells.
[4]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have four simultaneously scheduled EScells.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped in each DL subframe (TTI) for UEs using this cell as a PCell and which are activated with at least one ESCell.

column16: The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to WCDMA triggered either by CS Fallback or CS FallBack to WCDMA based on PSHO.\nScanner: Primary
column17: A CS Fallback attempt is performed towards a WCDMA Frequency, defined as an RRC Connection Release with redirect information, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback Required either in Initial Context Setup Request, or UE Context Modification Request. The counter steps either when release with redirect is preferred without measurement, or when handover is preferred but not possible, or when release with redirect based on measurement is preferred.

column16: Number of S1AP eDRX Paging messages routed to this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: When an S1AP eDRX Paging is routed to this cell which is correct and complete. An S1AP eDRX Paging message discarded as part of pmPagS1Discarded will not cause this counter to be pegged.

column16: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 8 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 1 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 8 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp.\nThe counter is defined according to 32.425.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17:
Samples summed over the measurement period. One sample per UE aperiodic rank 1 CQI report.
This counter is for rank 1 (one codeword) CQI reports.
The counter is defined according to 32.425 Section 4.10.1.2
Valid UE reported CQI values range from 0 to 15

column16:
Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to:
 - cell down time caused by a partial node restart (initiated automatically) or
 - automated UE recovery.
Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped for each E-RAB that is released due to cell down time (initiated automatically) caused by a partial node restart or due to automated UE recovery when data was in either the UL or DL buffer. In the UL case when a UE has multiple bearers co-existing and sharing the same LCG, the bearers share a single packet queue. If one of the bearers is released and there is data in the queue, the bearer's associated counter is incremented, regardless of whether or not the data belongs to the released bearer

column16: Peak number of UEs that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 3 and that are considered active in the UL direction. A UE is considered active if it has data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Set to peak sample recognized during the Recording Output Period (ROP).

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

Total of successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for SCell traffic as measured and reported on the PCell.\nUnit: kilobit (1 000 bits)\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when a DL transmission is acknowledged on HARQ level.

column16:
Distribution of the estimated SINR gain due to Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.

PDF ranges:
[0]: less than or equals to 1.0
[1]: ]1.0..2.0]
[2]: ]2.0..3.0]
...
[7]: ]7.0..8.0]
[8]: ]8.0..9.0]
[9]: greater than 9.0
Unit: dB
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when a SINR gain is applied to a UE scheduled in Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.

column16: Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to poor coverage in the SCell.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Accumulates when initiating SCell deconfiguration due to poor coverage indicated by a measurement report for event A2. Accumulates internal SCells only.

column16: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Data Radio Bearers (DRB) in the uplink when PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered. Used when feature NS_05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is activated and the attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled is configured to true.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Applies to DTCH on PUSCH.

column16: The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts that are considered as re-attempts for Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at reception of RRC message RRC Connection Request with Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access AND while an RRC Connection Setup is already ongoing for that S-TMSI.

column16:
Length of time the cell has been disabled due to:
- AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator
or
- the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily.
The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.
Unit: s
Scanner: Primary
column17: Incremented by one each second.

column16: The total number of failed RRC Connection Re-establishments due to RAC-BB signal queue congestion.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at transmission of RRC message RRC Reestablishment Reject when RAC-BB signal queue congestion was indicated.

column16: Number of successful outgoing, intra-LTE, inter-frequency handovers execution based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17:
Source eNodeB receives UE CONTEXT RELEASE from MME. Caused by S1 HO when A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement, RSRP triggered, has been reported from UE.
Or
Source eNodeB receives UE CONTEXT RELEASE from target eNodeB. Caused by X2 HO when A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement, RSRP triggered, has been reported from UE.
Or
Internal eNodeB trigger, corresponds to UE CONTEXT RELEASE, is received. Occurs when the UE changes cell during an intra-eNodeB HO when A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement, RSRP triggered, has been reported from UE.

column16: Number of successful DRS transmission attempts.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped for each successful DRS attempt.

column16:
Distribution of the UL UE throughput. One UL UE throughput sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers per UE, that has been received in the uplink direction, with a time interval applicable to the volume measurement. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

PDF ranges:
[0]: less than 10 kbps
[1]: [10..15[ kbps
[2]: [15..22[ kbps
[3]: [22..32[ kbps
[4]: [32..46[ kbps
[5]: [46..68[ kbps
[6]: [68..100[ kbps
[7]: [100..150[ kbps
[8]: [150..220[ kbps
[9]: [220..320[ kbps
[10]: [320..460[ kbps
[11]: [460..680[ kbps
[12]: [680..1000[ kbps
[13]: [1000..1500[ kbps
[14]: [1500..2200[ kbps
[15]: [2200..3200[ kbps
[16]: [3200..4600[ kbps
[17]: [4600..6800[ kbps
[18]: [6800..10000[ kbps
[19]: [10000..15000[ kbps
[20]: [15000..22000[ kbps
[21]: [22000..32000[ kbps
[22]: [32000..46000[ kbps
[23]: [46000..68000[ kbps
[24]: [68000..100000[ kbps
[25]: [100000..150000[ kbps
[26]: greater than or equals to 150000 kbps
Scanner: Primary
column17: One UL UE bit rate sample is added to the distribution for each completed UE data session, or at end of ROP.

column16:
Number of failed RRC Connection Establishments in the cell due to high SW component load on cell from bandwidth reduced UEs.

PDF ranges:
[0]: CE level 0
[1]: CE level 1
[2]: CE level 2
[3]: CE level 3
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at transmission of RRC Connection Reject due to high SW component load on cell from bandwidth reduced UEs.

column16: The total number of successful S1 signaling connection establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access.\nScanner: Primary
column17: Stepped at first message received on this UE-associated logical S1-connection, if the RRC Connection Request Establishment cause was Establishment cause Mobile Terminating Access.

column16: Number of periods that closed-loop power control in uplink select SINR based algorithm in the cell.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped after evaluation to choose SINR-based UL closed-loop power control algorithm.\nFeature must be enabled.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

The number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to static cell connection intensity control from bandwidth reduced UEs.

PDF ranges:
[0]: CE level 0
[1]: CE level 1
[2]: CE level 2
[3]: CE level 3
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at transmission of RRC Connection Establishments due to max static cell intensity reached from bandwidth reduced UEs.

column16:
Transfer time used for UL UE throughput. Comprised of the number of ms in which there is need for transmission on at least one of the LCGs specified in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::includeLcgInMacUeThp. Transfer time includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.
Unit: ms
Scanner: Primary
column17: Continuous measurement for each UE, aggregated to cell level.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
Total number of low-coverage UE RRC connection requests rejected by admission control.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when RRC connection request is rejected by low-coverage UE admission control.

column16: The number of failed handover preparations due to Procedure Latency Supervision.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at transmission of Handover Preparation Failed triggered by Procedure Latency Supervision.

column16: The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied.\nUnit: kilobit (1 000 bits)\nScanner: Primary
column17: Stepped before ROHC for UEs aggregated to cell level.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
The accumulated interference power for PRB66\nUnit: mW * 2^(-44)\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Samples summed over the measurement period. Measurements are averaged over receive antennas. One sample for each PRB per 40ms.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME that occurred during the extended inactivity time and that had a cause regarded as abnormal.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at reception of S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release with none of the following causes: Normal Release, Handover Successful, User Inactivity, Detach, CS Fallback Triggered, Inter-RAT Redirection, UE Not available for PS Service or Redirection towards 1xRTT. This must occur during the extended inactivity time. The release must also be MME initiated.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

Number of RRC connection releases with redirect to CDMA FDD, triggered when critical UL coverage reached\nThis counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when RRC connection release with redirect to CDMA FDD is triggered by critical UL coverage.

column16:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on Data Radio Bearers in the downlink direction per QCI.

Compressed: True
Unit: kilobit (1 000 bits)
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Measures DL PDCP volume for UM and AM for each QCI before ROHC.

column16:
Number of added E-RAB establishment requests rejected by Differentiated Admission Control due to MSR capacity within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.

PDF ranges:
[0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value)
[1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1
...
[15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15

Compressed: True
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The bin for the corresponding ARP priority level is stepped when added E-RAB establishment requests are rejected by Differentiated Admission Control due to capacity exceeded on any MSR. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

column16:
Number of supported LAA SCell CCs that support DL, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.

PDF ranges:
[0]: Number of UEs that are not DL LAA CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only
[1]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus one LAA SCell
[2]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus two LAA SCells
[3]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus three LAA SCells
[4]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus four LAA SCells
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: When UE capability is registered, the counter that corresponds to the maximum number of downlink LAA SCells is incremented. When UE capability is deregistered, the counter that corresponds is decremented.

column16: Number of times that the low ARP prioritized DRB are resumed.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when a low ARP prioritized DRB is resumed regarding RLC DL due to a RRC Connection Re-establishment or a HO has been performed.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
The number of RRC Connection Release triggered by CS Fallback for Limited Dual Radio UE LTE/1xRTT.\nScanner: Primary
column17: A CS Fallback attempt is performed for a limited Dual Radio UE towards CDMA2000 1xRTT, defined as a RRC Connection Release, due to a received CS Fallback Indicator set to CS Fallback Required in Initial Context Setup Request or UE Context Modification Request.

column16: Maximum (high-water mark) value of UL PRB capacity usage, excluding PRBs used for traffic from bandwidth-reduced UEs.\nUnit: PRB\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Set to max value recognized during each ROP.

column16:
Abnormal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS (per cell per ARP). Stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL or DL buffers.

PDF ranges:
[0]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0
[1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1
....
[15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at reception of S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release Command, with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed, for E-RAB/s with the specific ARP Priority Level, when internal cause codes considered abnormal (Radio Connection with UE is lost; Handover failure for the UE; Non admitted E-RABs by target cell at successful handover for the UE; UE pre-emption; Bearer pre-emption) when the RBS initiated the release. It can also be stepped at transmission of Reset message by the RBS, or when a cell owned by that RBS is disabled (and that leads to internal RBS UE Context Release).

column16: The total number of unicast short-SPS uplink grants confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Incremented by 1 when a short-SPS grant is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

column16: Maximum utilization of CQI resources in the medium resource pool.\nUnit: %\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: When pool resource utilization increased after a successful CQI resource allocation in the pool.

column16:
Total PRB pairs available in center region (PRB24~75 except for PUCCH) for UL transmission. Used when feature NS_05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is activated.

Since 17.Q4. Replaces pmZtemporary235.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Applies to PUSCH.

column16: The total amount of physical resources used for transmission in the uplink. Both successful and unsuccessful transmissions are counted.\nUnit: Resource Elements * 1000\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented when an uplink transmission is received, regardless of whether the reception was successful or not.

column16: The number of failed handover preparations triggered by the MP overload state.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at transmission of Handover Preparation Failure message when triggered by MP in overload state.

column16: The time where the UE have uplink data in a buffer and End-user bitrate shaping functionality will prohibit transmission in the uplink.\nUnit: ms\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Data in uplink buffer, according to the Buffer Status Report (BSR) and Token Bucket Counter (TBC) less than 0. Continuous measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level.

column16:
Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to:
 - cell down time initiated automatically caused by a partial node restart or
 - automated UE recovery.
Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Compressed: True
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped for each E-RAB. Maps to a certain QCI that is released due to automatically initiated cell down time caused by a partial node restart or due to automated UE recovery when data is in the UL or DL buffer. In the UL case, when a UE has multiple bearers coexisting and sharing the same LCG, the bearers share a single packet queue. If one of the bearers is released and there is data in the queue, the associated counter for the bearer is incremented, regardless of whether or not the data belongs to the released bearer.

column16: The accumulated interference power for PRB2\nUnit: mW * 2^(-44)\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Samples summed over the measurement period. Measurements are averaged over receive antennas. One sample for each PRB per 40ms.

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is unknown.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: It is pegged if eNB cannot determine if a unicast DL assignment is received by a UE that uses this cell as the primary cell and does not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.\nThe counter is pegged when licenses for both CarrierAggregation and EnhancedPdcchLa are enabled, and CarrierAggregation feature is activated.

column16:
Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

Deprecated: Since L16B. Planned to be removed
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped if the UE is a PFT user in Out-of-Sync state and the UE Context release is due to handover failure.

column16:
PDF of percentage of CCEs utilized compared with total CCEs available (at the maximum CFI permitted by pdcchCfiMode) each subframe, considering bandwidth and antenna configuration.

PDF ranges:
[0]: utilization less than or equals to 5%
[1]: 5% less than utilization less than or equals to 10%
[2]: 10% less than utilization less than or equals to 15%
[3]: 15% less than utilization less than or equals to 20%
[4]: 20% less than utilization less than or equals to 25%
[5]: 25% less than utilization less than or equals to 30%
[6]: 30% less than utilization less than or equals to 35%
[7]: 35% less than utilization less than or equals to 40%
[8]: 40% less than utilization less than or equals to 45%
[9]: 45% less than utilization less than or equals to 50%
[10]: 50% less than utilization less than or equals to 55%
[11]: 55% less than utilization less than or equals to 60%
[12]: 60% less than utilization less than or equals to 65%
[13]: 65% less than utilization less than or equals to 70%
[14]: 70% less than utilization less than or equals to 75%
[15]: 75% less than utilization less than or equals to 80%
[16]: 80% less than utilization less than or equals to 85%
[17]: 85% less than utilization less than or equals to 90%
[18]: 90% less than utilization less than or equals to 95%
[19]: 95% less than utilization less than or equals to 100%

In subframes where the number of available CCEs is zero, the lowest bin is incremented.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Appropriate bin is incremented every radio subframe.

column16: Number of UE Context Fetch procedures successfully completed during X2 handover execution.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: X2 UE Context Release message is received from target eNodeB after successful UE Context Fetch procedure. UE Context Fetch procedure was triggered during X2 handover execution.

column16: Number of UE Context Fetch Request messages received during intra-eNodeB handover execution.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Unprepared target eNodeB received RRC Connection Reestablishment message. The target eNodeB triggers UE Context Fetch procedure to fetch UE context. UE Context Fetch Request message is received in source cell during intra-eNodeB handover execution.

column16:
Peak number of Cat-M UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Deprecated: Since 17.Q2. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Set to peak number of Cat-M UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode, recognized at end of each ROP.

column16: Number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the UL direction that use a 64-QAM modulation.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped at measurement for each UE, aggregated to cell level.

column16: Total number of successful RRC Connection Reconfiguration attempts for configuration of event A5 used in Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when an RRC Connection Reconfiguration Complete message is received from the UE following event A5 configuration for Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.

column16: The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the uplink direction.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Each TTI, the counter shall be increased with the number of DRBs that are considered active (i.e. that are considered to have data in the uplink buffer).

column16:
NS_05 UE UL transmission time, used for UL DRB throughput for each LCG. Comprised of time periods from when 5th data transmission is received on Uu until second from last data transmission is received. Used when feature NS_05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is activated.

Since 17.Q4. Replaces pmZtemporary232Compr.
Unit: ms
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Bin accumulates NS_05 UEs' UL transmission time for each LCG for large data bursts that need to be transmitted across multiple TTIs.\nAssociated pmCounter pmLcgThpVolUlNs05Distr.

column16: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: It is pegged when a unicast UL grant is transmitted to a UE that uses this cell as the primary cell and does not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, excluding the UL grants for message 3 for RRC connection setup.\nThe counter is pegged when licenses for both CarrierAggregation and EnhancedPdcchLa are enabled, and CarrierAggregation feature is activated.

column16: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 7 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 2 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 7 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqi2SubbandSamp.\nThe counter is defined according to 32.425.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17:
Samples summed over the measurement period. One sample per UE aperiodic rank 2 CQI report.
This counter is for rank 2 (two codewords) CQI reports.
The counter is defined according to 32.425 Section 4.10.1.2

column16: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of unsatisfactory quality.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented when the VoIP session, i.e. the time when a radio bearer which carries VoIP traffic is established, has had an unsatisfactory VoIP quality. This can be caused by two conditions: (1) At least the minimum required amount of VoIP packets are available for the measurement and less than 99% of the VoIP packets for the VoIP session had an air interface delay within the packet delay budget. (2) 50% or less of the VoIP packets of the VoIP session had an air interface delay within the packet delay budget, regardless of the amount of VoIP packets for measurement. If the above conditions are met then counters can be incremented at the end of the ROP (Recording Output Period) or when the voice bearer is released by ERAB Release procedure or both of them.

column16:
The Counter is incremented every time a calibration attempt is unsuccessful. A set of measurements are preformed every calibration occasion. If the calibration is successful or not is determined by two tests:

1: A test to check if the level of the received calibration measurement signal is to low.

2: A test to check if the signal is disturbed or corrupted in a way that it is not possible to estimate the calibration parameters.

If at least one of the tests are failing the calibration is considered unsuccessful and the counter is incremented. If calibration is unsuccessful a new calibration attempt is immediately started. After several unsuccessful calibration attempts an alarm is issued.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented for each unsuccessful calibration attempt.

The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is set to peak sample recognized at the end of each Recording Output Period (ROP).

column16: Total EUTRAN HOs, intra-frequency and inter-frequency, prevented prior to HO preparation because target cell PLMN is not whitelisted in serving cell.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when best HO target cell PLMN is not whitelisted in serving cell. From traffic measurement reports, A3 or A5.

column16: The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME considered as abnormal. The counter is stepped if there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).\nScanner: Primary
column17: Stepped at reception of S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release with none of the causes Normal Release, Handover Successful, User Inactivity, Detach, CS Fallback Triggered, Inter-RAT Redirection, UE Not available for PS Service or Redirection towards 1xRTT and there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active). The release must also have been MME initiated. In the UL case when a UE has multiple bearers co-existing and sharing the same LCG, the bearers share a single packet queue. If one of the bearers is released and there is data in the queue, the bearer's associated counter  is incremented, regardless of whether or not the data belongs to the released bearer.

column16: The accumulated interference power for PRB25\nUnit: mW * 2^(-44)\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Samples summed over the measurement period. Measurements are averaged over receive antennas. One sample for each PRB per 40ms.

column16:
Number of RRC connection releases with redirect to CDMA2000 1xRtt, triggered when critical UL coverage reached.
This counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

Deprecated: Since 17.Q4. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
Scanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when RRC connection release with redirect to CDMA2000 1xRtt is triggered by critical UL coverage.

column16: The number of UE that are not satisfied with their VoIP quality.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented when it has been determined that a UE is not satisfied with its VoIP quality. This can be caused due to two conditions: (1) At least the minimume amount of VoIP packets is available for the measurement and less than 99% of the VoIP packets of the UE had an air interface delay within the packet delay budget.  (2)  50% or less of the VoIP packets of the UE had an air interface delay within the packet delay budget, regardless of the amount of VoIP packets for measurement.

column16: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 10 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 2 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 10 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqi2SubbandSamp.\nThe counter is defined according to 32.425.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17:
Samples summed over the measurement period. One sample per UE aperiodic rank 2 CQI report.
This counter is for rank 2 (two codewords) CQI reports.
The counter is defined according to 32.425 Section 4.10.1.2
Valid UE reported CQI values range from 0 to 15
Note for CQI/PMI/RI reporting mode 3-1 or 2-1, there will be a different Sub-band CQI value for each codeword. In this case both CQI values shall be added to the counter and are counted as two samples.

column16: Total number of measurement reports received from the UE.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: Stepped when a measurement report is received from the UE.

column16: Number of TTIs for which CRS:es in the PDCCH region are fully or partially blanked.\nUnit: subframes\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: When ELC decides to mute parts of the CRS:es that are contained in the PDCCH region, this counter is stepped once.

column16: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of satisfactory quality.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner
column17: The counter is incremented when the VoIP session, i.e. the time when a radio bearer which carries VoIP traffic is established, has had a satisfactory VoIP quality. This means that at least the minimum required amount of VoIP packets are available for the measurement, and that at least 99% of the VoIP packets for the VoIP session had an air interface delay within the packet delay budget. If the above conditions are met then counters can be incremented at the end of the ROP (Recording output period) or when the voice bearer is released by ERAB Release procedure or both of them

column16:

[1]: Number of times non-carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Release 8 multiplexing as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode

column16: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI because contact with the UE is lost. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed.\nCompressed: true.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

column16: Number of setups Robust Header Compression failed due to missing or inoperable license.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

column16:

column16: Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.\nScanner: Not included in any predefined scanner

column17: The effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering the buffer until the first data has been transmitted to the UE. Measurement for UEs aggregated to cell level. Only PDCP SDUs that enters an empty buffer are measured. Samples during handover are excluded since they can distort the interpretation of the result (due to packet forwarding, the target cell might have to buffer data before it is possible to schedule the UE in the target cell, hence it would be an increased Latency measurement if it would be included. column16:
Distribution of PIM signal power injected to cancel (by subtraction) the PIM for all UL carrier branches in PIM Cancellation group.
PDF ranges:
[0]:      .. 0.1[ dBc
[1]: [0.1 .. 1.0[ dBc
[2]: [1.0 .. 2.0[ dBc
[3]: [2.0 .. 3.0[ dBc
...
[28]: [27.0 .. 28.0[ dBc
[29]: [28.0 .. 29.0[ dBc
[30]: [29.0 ..       dBc
column17: Appropriate bin is incremented every sampling interval.

column16:
Distribution of PIM Cancellation coefficients divergence states for the PIM Cancellation group.
PDF ranges:
[0]: coefficientsUnknown. Coefficients of the estimation algorithm have not converged yet.
[1]: coefficientsConverging. Coefficients of the estimation algorithm are converging.
[2]: coefficientsDiverging. Coefficients of the estimation algorithm are diverging slightly but are within acceptable limits.
[3]: coefficientsAbnormal. Coefficient divergence of the estimation algorithm has exceeded acceptable limits. PIM Cancellation injection has stopped.
column17: Appropriate bin is incremented every sampling interval.

column16:
Distribution of PIM Cancellation group states.
PDF ranges:

column10: Contains all PM counters for DlPowerSharing
column16: The number of power-limited slots during a granularity period.
column17: The actual measurement is started when the sector is initiated, and at least one carrier branch is enabled on the downlink rfBranch, and the feature HSDPA Mixed Mode Power Sharing is activated. Each power-limited slot detected on the downlink rfBranch increases the count by 1. This occurs when the traffic load for the rfBranch is too high.

column16: Number outgoing packets that have been discarded because there is no Child SA established with a traffic selector matching the packet.
The number of incoming ESP packets that have been discarded because they failed the integrity check.
The number of incoming ESP packets that have been discarded due to that they failed the antireplay check
